                 triggers the scroll came.</param>
        <summary>Returns whether a view should smooth scroll when scrolling due to a <c>MotionEvent</c>
            generated by the input device.</summary>
        <returns>
          <c>true</c> if smooth scrolling should be used for the scroll, or <c>false</c>
                 if smooth scrolling is not necessary, or if the provided axis and source combination
                 is not available for the input device.</returns>
        <remarks>
          <para>Returns whether a view should smooth scroll when scrolling due to a <c>MotionEvent</c>
            generated by the input device.</para>
          <para>Smooth scroll in this case refers to a scroll that animates the transition between
            the starting and ending positions of the scroll. When this method returns <c>true</c>,
            views should try to animate a scroll generated by this device at the given axis and with
            the given source to produce a good scroll user experience. If this method returns
            <c>false</c>, animating scrolls is not necessary.</para>
          <para>If the input device does not have a <c>MotionRange</c> with the provided axis and
            source, this method returns <c>false</c>.</para>
          <para>
            <format type="text/html">
              <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/InputDevice.ViewBehavior#shouldSmoothScroll(int,%20int)" title="Reference documentation">Java documentation for <code>android.view.InputDevice.ViewBehavior.shouldSmoothScroll(int, int)</code>.</a>
